{"type":"message","id":"43135b69","parentId":"5517a5ac","timestamp":"2026-04-13T02:22:16.197Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_631a5280-af6d-4ffc-a9e1-1a6ab2afae44","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"error\": \"missing_brave_api_key\",\n  \"message\": \"web_search (brave) needs a Brave Search API key. Run `openclaw configure --section web` to store it, or set BRAVE_API_KEY in the Gateway environment.\",\n  \"docs\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/tools/web\"\n}"}],"details":{"error":"missing_brave_api_key","message":"web_search (brave) needs a Brave Search API key. Run `openclaw configure --section web` to store it, or set BRAVE_API_KEY in the Gateway environment.","docs":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/tools/web"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776046936193}}
{"type":"message","id":"b16ec411","parentId":"43135b69","timestamp":"2026-04-13T02:22:39.255Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I encountered an issue with fetching the latest AI news from the last 24 hours using diffusers. It seems that a Brave Search API key is required for this operation. Running `openclaw configure --section web` could help store the API key, or setting the environment variable BRAAVE_API_KEY directly would also work.\n\nHere’s what I suggest:\n\n1. **Configure Browser Settings:**\n   - Run the command `openclaw configure --section web`. This will prompt you to enter your Brave Search API key.\n   - Alternatively, you can set the environment variable by running `export BRAVE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here`.\n\n2. **Directly Set Environment Variable:**\n   - You can also directly set the environment variable with your API key before performing any web searches.\n\nOnce you have configured this properly, try searching for the latest AI news again using the `web_search` function. Here’s an example of how to configure Brave:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw configure --section web\n```\n\nPlease follow these steps and let me know if you need further assistance with configuring Brave settings or performing your search.\n"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"qwen-local:latest","usage":{"input":8198,"output":229,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8427,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1776046959251}}
